column18: 07/11/2005: A bomb planted in a garbage can in Trinidad & Tobago injured 14 people in the city of Port-of-Spain. No one claimed responsibility for the attack.

column58: Coordination of the United Revolutionary Organization (CORU)

column18: 08/10/2005: Unknown perpetrators planted a small bomb in a trash bin that exploded in Port-of-Spain, Trinidad and Tobago. The bomb did not result in any casualties or damage. No group claimed responsibility for the attack.
column97: The bomb was placed in a trash bin.
column125: Local radicals were suspected of planting the device. The incident was the second bombing in Port-of-Spain in 33 days.
